## Summary Table: Market Failure Characteristics in Pollution

| Aspect                          | Description                                                                                         | Impact on Market Efficiency                 |
|--------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| Negative Externality            | Pollution imposes costs on third parties not involved in production or consumption               | Leads to overproduction and overconsumption |
| Discrepancy in Costs           | Private costs < Social costs due to unaccounted externalities                                    | Market prices do not reflect true costs     |
| Absence of Pollution Market     | No direct market for pollution rights or environmental quality                                   | Firms lack incentives to reduce pollution   |
| Common Resource Problem         | Pollution affects shared resources like air and water                                           | Overexploitation and "tragedy of the commons" |
| Inefficient Resource Allocation | Firms prioritize profit, ignoring social costs                                                  | Results in welfare loss and economic inefficiency |
| Global Externalities            | Pollution crosses borders, affecting global commons                                             | Requires international cooperation           |

